<TITLE>PIGLIT</TITLE>

<H1>PIGLIT (Patient Information Generated by Loosely Intelligent Techniques)</H1>

<IMG SRC="http://www.dcs.gla.ac.uk/~alison/pig.gif"> <P>

Welcome to the PIGLIT pages. If you have any questions or comments,
please contact me (alison@dcs.gla.ac.uk). 

<H2>Introduction</H2>

PIGLIT (sometimes known as PIGLET) is a project in the <A HREF="/">Computing Science</A> (<A HREF="http://www.dcs.gla.ac.uk/~alison">Alison
Cawsey</A> and <A HREF="http://www.dcs.gla.ac.uk/~kimb">Kim Binsted</A>)
and Public Health (Ray Jones) departments of the <A
HREF="gopher://gopher.gla.ac.uk">University of Glasgow</A>. The idea
is to develop a system which generates personalised, hypertext
explanations of patient records, for patients.

